body:
> Thanks for taking the time to report this.
> 
> Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
> 

```
interface bad_if #(A=0, N=0);
  bit [A-1:0] addr;
  bit [(N*8)-1:0] data;
endinterface

class bad_class #(A=0, N=0);  
   virtual bad_if #(A, N) vif;
   
   function new(virtual bad_if #(A, N) _vif);
      vif = _vif;
   endfunction  
endclass

module top;
  localparam A = 8;
  localparam N = 2;

   bad_if #(A, N) the_if();
   bad_class bc_h;

   initial begin
      bc_h = new(the_if);
      #100;
      $finish;
   end
endmodule
```

> What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

verilator --binary --exe --timing ./bad_if.sv

> What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?

Verilator 5.028 2024-08-21 rev v5.028

> What OS and distribution are you using?

windows 11 on WSL Ubuntu-24.04

`May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?`

I wouldn't have a clue where to start. 

> (Please avoid attaching screenshots that show text - you can convert images to text using e.g. https://ocr.space)


Here's the error message.

%Error-UNSUPPORTED: bad_if.sv:8:12: Unsupported: virtual interface never assigned any actual interface
                                  : ... note: In instance 'top'
    8 |    virtual bad_if #(A, N) vif;
      |            ^~~~~~
                    ... For error description see https://verilator.org/warn/UNSUPPORTED?v=5.028
%Error-UNSUPPORTED: bad_if.sv:10:25: Unsupported: virtual interface never assigned any actual interface
                                   : ... note: In instance 'top'
   10 |    function new(virtual bad_if #(A, N) _vif);
      |                         ^~~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 2 error(s)
        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.

It works just fine if the port parameters are removed, like below.

```
interface bad_if ;
  localparam A = 8;
  localparam N = 2;
  bit [A-1:0] addr;
  bit [(N*8)-1:0] data;
endinterface

class bad_class ;  
   virtual bad_if vif;
   
   function new(virtual bad_if _vif);
      vif = _vif;
   endfunction  
endclass

module top;
  localparam A = 8;
  localparam N = 2;

   bad_if the_if();
   bad_class bc_h;

   initial begin
      bc_h = new(the_if);
      #100;
      $finish;
   end
endmodule
```
